description: The Mediterranean Sea or Mare Nostrum is a sea connected to the Atlantic Ocean that is surrounded almost completely by land.
details: Also called Our Sea by Greeks and Romans, this is the entire body of water between the Straits of Gibraltar and the coast of Syria.
